# Calculator diagrams

Open preview in Cursor: **Ctrl+Shift+V** (Windows) or **Cmd+Shift+V** (Mac) — or right-click → **Open Preview**.

---

## 1. Module structure

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph runtime [Runtime]
        entry([Program start])
    end

    subgraph app [calculator.c]
        main["main()"]
        add["add(a, b)"]
        subtract["subtract(a, b)"]
        multiply["multiply(a, b)"]
        divide["divide(a, b)"]
        modulo["modulo(a, b)"]
    end

    subgraph libc [stdio.h]
        printf["printf"]
        scanf["scanf"]
    end

    entry --> main
    main --> printf
    main --> scanf
    main -->|"choice == 1"| add
    main -->|"choice == 2"| subtract
    main -->|"choice == 3"| multiply
    main -->|"choice == 4, y != 0"| divide
    main -->|"choice == 5, x,y >= 0, y != 0"| modulo
```

---

## 2. Program flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    start([main]) --> showMenu["printf: menu"]
    showMenu --> readInput["scanf: choice, x, y"]
    readInput --> route{choice?}

    route -->|1| callAdd["add(x, y)"]
    route -->|2| callSub["subtract(x, y)"]
    route -->|3| callMul["multiply(x, y)"]
    route -->|4| checkZero{y == 0?}
    route -->|5| checkNeg{x < 0 or y < 0?}
    route -->|other| invalid["printf: Invalid choice"]

    callAdd --> printOk["printf: Result"]
    callSub --> printOk
    callMul --> printOk

    checkZero -->|no| callDiv["divide(x, y)"]
    checkZero -->|yes| divErr["printf: Division by zero"]
    callDiv --> printOk

    checkNeg -->|yes| modNegErr["printf: Modulo requires non-negative operands"]
    checkNeg -->|no| checkModZero{y == 0?}
    checkModZero -->|no| callMod["modulo(x, y)"]
    checkModZero -->|yes| modErr["printf: Modulo by zero"]
    callMod --> printOk

    printOk --> exit([return 0])
    divErr --> exit
    modNegErr --> exit
    modErr --> exit
    invalid --> exit
```

