## 3. Function API

```mermaid
classDiagram
    direction TB
    class main {
        +int main()
    }
    class add {
        +int add(int a, int b)
    }
    class subtract {
        +int subtract(int a, int b)
    }
    class multiply {
        +int multiply(int a, int b)
    }
    class divide {
        +int divide(int a, int b)
    }
    class modulo {
        +int modulo(int a, int b)
    }
    class stdio {
        printf()
        scanf()
    }

    main --> stdio : uses
    main --> add : case 1
    main --> subtract : case 2
    main --> multiply : case 3
    main --> divide : case 4
    main --> modulo : case 5
```

---

## 4. Sequence

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant main
    participant op as add/subtract/multiply/divide/modulo

    User->>main: choice, x, y
    alt choice 1
        main->>op: add(x, y)
    else choice 2
        main->>op: subtract(x, y)
    else choice 3
        main->>op: multiply(x, y)
    else choice 4 and y != 0
        main->>op: divide(x, y)
    else choice 4 and y == 0
        main-->>User: Division by zero error
    else choice 5 and x,y >= 0 and y != 0
        main->>op: modulo(x, y)
    else choice 5 and negative operand
        main-->>User: Modulo requires non-negative operands
    else choice 5 and y == 0
        main-->>User: Modulo by zero error
    else invalid choice
        main-->>User: Invalid choice
    end
    op-->>main: result
    main-->>User: Result printed
```
